    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Fuel System - Periodic Servicing - Fuel
        Filter
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="S2651201" svcproctype="drain" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Fuel Filter</title>
        <figure id="f2651246" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/h11023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Fuel drain valve in open position</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move yellow water drain valve assembly to the open position and drain fuel into a suitable
                container.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651247" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/h11027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Fuel filter element</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unthread housing cover and fuel filter as an assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull fuel filter from housing cover and discard O-ring gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new O-ring gasket onto housing cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new fuel filter onto housing cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate housing cover threads and O-ring gasket with diesel fuel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread fuel filter and housing cover in as an assembly. Torque to the special value .</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
